{"questionId":"13022","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = {\\text{sec}}\\,x + 2\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sec</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 \\leqslant x < \\frac{\\pi }{2}\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'\\left( x \\right)\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></math></span>, stating its domain.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = {\\text{sec}}\\,y + 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mtext>sec</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>y</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Exchange of variables can take place at any point.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{cos}}\\,y = \\frac{1}{{x - 2}}\"> <mrow> <mtext>cos</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f'\\left( x \\right) = {\\text{arccos}}\\left( {\\frac{1}{{x - 2}}} \\right)\"> <msup> <mi>f</mi> <mo>′</mo> </msup> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mtext>arccos</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>&nbsp;≥ 3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Allow follow through from (a) for last <em><strong>A1</strong></em> mark which is independent of earlier marks in (b).</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13022","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_4b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find f-1(x), stating its domain.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.14—Odd and even functions, self-inverse, inverse and domain restriction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}